title: Shavasan
description: Shavasan, also known as the Corpse Pose, is a relaxation pose that helps in reducing stress, calming the mind, and promoting a sense of tranquility.

title: SIRSASANA
description: excellent for improving concentration, increasing memory, and transforming libido into powerful life force

title: SARVANGASANA
description: This asana strengthens the entire body; it gives many of the benefits of the Headstand, but here the circulation is directed to the thyroid gland instead of the head.

title: HALASANA
description: It stretches the back of the body completely which invigorates the entire spine. It also loosens tight hamstrings.

title: MATSYASANA
description: it is very effective in correcting any tendency to round the shoulders as well as helping to tone the nerves of the neck and the back area.

title: PASCIMOTHANASANA
description: helps to counter the typical postural problems developed working a desk job by keeping the spine supple, the joints mobile, the internal organs toned, and the nervous system invigorated.

title: Jumping jacks
description: strengthen your muscles, improve coordination, and boost your fitness.

title: Trunk twists
description: improve core strength, stability, flexibility and provide greater spine mobility.

title: Push-ups
description: strengthen and tone upper-body muscles, including your chest, triceps, and shoulders.

title: Pull-ups
description: a good exercise to challenge your arm, shoulder, and back muscles.

title: Chin-ups
description: Improvements in grip strength. Improvements to your posture. A lowered chance of upper back pain and shoulder injury. A decreased risk for heart problems, obesity, and other health issues

title: Sit-ups
description: Core strength is one of the biggest motivators for doing situps. Situps build muscle strength in the abdominal and hip muscles.

title: Plank
description: The plank position helps target the core muscles and give them a good burn to build muscle strength.

title: Crisscross
description: Challenges pelvic stability and control. Works the obliques which not only helps build a strong core, but also helps define the waist. Challenges your entire core system and breathing mechanics.

title: Roll down
description: stretches the back and the hamstrings along the back of our legs and is great for improving our posture.

title: Leg pull front prep
description: Strengthens and tones the arms, seat, and legs. Stretches the achilles tendon. Creates stability and control in the whole body. Lengthens the body from the crown of the head to toes.

title: Swan dive
description: works the back, abdominals, glutes, hamstrings and inner thighs. It will strengthen the back of the body while stretching out the front of the body, making it a full-body exercise.

title: Side leg lifts
description: better range of motion in the hips. better body stabilization. use of muscles that aren't usually active in those who sit for prolonged periods each day. improved muscle endurance.

title: Deadlifts
description: Deadlifts are a compound exercise that targets multiple muscle groups, including the lower back, hamstrings, and glutes, promoting overall strength and stability.

title: Bench Press
description: The bench press is a classic upper body strength training exercise that primarily works the chest, shoulders, and triceps.

title: Overhead Press
description: The overhead press, or shoulder press, is an exercise that targets the deltoid muscles of the shoulder, as well as the triceps and upper back.

title: Lunges
description: Lunges are a lower body exercise that targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes, helping to improve leg strength and stability.

title: Chest Flyes
description: Chest flyes are an isolation exercise that targets the pectoral muscles, helping to develop and define the chest.

title: Hammer Curls
description: Hammer curls are a bicep exercise that targets the brachialis and brachioradialis muscles, contributing to overall arm strength.

title: Sprinting
description: Sprinting is an explosive cardiovascular exercise that enhances speed, agility, and cardiovascular health.

title: Hill Running
description: Running uphill engages different muscles and adds intensity to your workout. It builds strength in your legs, enhances cardiovascular fitness, and can improve overall running performance.

title: Interval Training
description: Interval training involves alternating between high-intensity running and periods of rest or lower intensity. It helps improve cardiovascular fitness, speed, and endurance. Example: 30 seconds sprint followed by 1 minute jog.

title: Burpees
description: Burpees are a full-body exercise used in HIIT workouts, promoting cardiovascular fitness, strength, and endurance.

title: Tabata Workout
description: Tabata is a specific form of HIIT, consisting of 20 seconds of all-out effort followed by 10 seconds of rest, repeated for four minutes. It's a quick but intense workout that can be adapted to various exercises.

title: Bodyweight HIIT
description: Bodyweight HIIT workouts are convenient and can be done anywhere. Exercises may include squats, lunges, burpees, and push-ups. The focus is on using your own body as resistance for a challenging workout.

title: HIIT for Fat Loss
description: HIIT is known for its effectiveness in burning fat. The high-intensity intervals elevate heart rate and metabolism, promoting fat burning during and after the workout. It also helps preserve muscle mass.
